obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_5348  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 8: Cultured hippocampal neurons overexpressing RNF34 show reduced density of endogenous γ2-GABAAR clusters and reduced GABAergic innervations.\n\"These results show that overexpression of RNF34 significantly decreases the number of γ2-GABAAR clusters in the transfected neurons and the number of GABAergic contacts that the transfected neurons receive, and these effects depend on the E3 UBL activity of RNF34.\"\n\nFigure 9: Knocking down endogenous RNF34 in cultured hippocampal neurons increases both the γ2-GABAAR cluster density and GABAergic innervation.. Experimental description: Results, Figure 7 legend: \"postembedding EM immunogold double-labeling of rat brain cerebellum\"\n\nantibody:\n\"rabbit (Rb) polyclonal antiserum to RNF34 (anti-RNF34) was generated after immunizing with a C-terminal peptide of the rat RNF34 protein (aa 368-381, CRQYVVRAVHVFKS). The antigenic peptide sequence is identical in human, rat, and mouse\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-12" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5348" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

